"{\"uid\": \"jamaicaobserver.com-2024-07-30-biles-chases-first-paris-olympic-gold-fingers-crossed-seine\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"PARIS, France (AFP) - Simone Biles is tipped to win her first Olympic gymnastics gold since 2016 on Tuesday while Paris organisers will be nervously monitoring pollution levels in the River Seine ahead of the men's triathlon.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 225, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7, \"end\": 13, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9036474985742077, \"rank\": 0.09992562621082521, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 114, \"end\": 119, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999852207, \"rank\": 1.4678697064861324e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 184, \"end\": 195, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"PARIS\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 5}, {\"ngram\": \"AFP\", \"from\": 15, \"to\": 18}, {\"ngram\": \"Simone Biles\", \"from\": 22, \"to\": 34}, {\"ngram\": \"her first Olympic gymnastics gold\", \"from\": 52, \"to\": 85}, {\"ngram\": \"Tuesday\", \"from\": 100, \"to\": 107}, {\"ngram\": \"pollution levels\", \"from\": 160, \"to\": 176}, {\"ngram\": \"the men's triathlon\", \"from\": 205, \"to\": 224}]}, {\"sentence\": \"America's Biles appears to be back at the peak of her powers as she leads the United States on what has been billed as a redemption mission in the women's team final.\", \"from\": 227, \"to\": 393, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 305, \"end\": 318, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9996836196410273, \"rank\": 0.00030702498960177095, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"America's Biles\", \"from\": 227, \"to\": 242}, {\"ngram\": \"the peak\", \"from\": 265, \"to\": 273}, {\"ngram\": \"her powers\", \"from\": 277, \"to\": 287}, {\"ngram\": \"a redemption mission\", \"from\": 346, \"to\": 366}, {\"ngram\": \"the women's team\", \"from\": 370, \"to\": 386}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 27-year-old, considered the greatest gymnast of all time, won four gold medals at the Rio 2016 Games.\", \"from\": 395, \"to\": 500, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 485, \"end\": 488, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999997905001912, \"rank\": 2.0949987718290127e-07, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the greatest gymnast\", \"from\": 423, \"to\": 443}, {\"ngram\": \"all time\", \"from\": 447, \"to\": 455}, {\"ngram\": \"four gold medals\", \"from\": 461, \"to\": 477}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But she battled the disorientating mental block gymnasts call the \\\"twisties\\\" at the pandemic-delayed Tokyo Olympics three years ago.\", \"from\": 502, \"to\": 634, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the disorientating mental block gymnasts\", \"from\": 518, \"to\": 558}, {\"ngram\": \"the \\\"twisties\", \"from\": 564, \"to\": 577}, {\"ngram\": \"the pandemic-delayed Tokyo Olympics\", \"from\": 582, \"to\": 617}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Biles dramatically pulled out of most of her events, including the team final, and the United States settled for silver behind Russia after winning gold in 2012 and 2016.\", \"from\": 636, \"to\": 806, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 723, \"end\": 736, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9996836196410273, \"rank\": 0.00030702498960177095, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 763, \"end\": 769, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.926373924999903, \"rank\": 0.06796308592231251, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Biles\", \"from\": 636, \"to\": 641}, {\"ngram\": \"her events\", \"from\": 677, \"to\": 687}, {\"ngram\": \"the team\", \"from\": 699, \"to\": 707}, {\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 749, \"to\": 755}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 784, \"to\": 788}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Biles, a 23-time world champion, went home with a silver and a bronze, and while she won many plaudits for opening up on her mental health, there were critics who accused her of putting herself before her country.\", \"from\": 808, \"to\": 1021, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Biles\", \"from\": 808, \"to\": 813}, {\"ngram\": \"a 23-time world champion\", \"from\": 815, \"to\": 839}, {\"ngram\": \"a silver\", \"from\": 856, \"to\": 864}, {\"ngram\": \"a bronze\", \"from\": 869, \"to\": 877}, {\"ngram\": \"many plaudits\", \"from\": 897, \"to\": 910}, {\"ngram\": \"her mental health\", \"from\": 929, \"to\": 946}, {\"ngram\": \"critics\", \"from\": 959, \"to\": 966}, {\"ngram\": \"her country\", \"from\": 1009, \"to\": 1020}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It has to be for us,\\\" Biles said of the United States' bid to recapture their women's team crown.\", \"from\": 1023, \"t